<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>VT 365 Diesel Engine - 2004 Model Year - MANIFOLDS AND EXHAUST GAS RECIRCULATION (EGR) - Removal - Intake
        Manifold and EGR Cooler
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s26503.2.3" svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="6">
        <title>Intake Manifold and EGR Cooler</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Before removing intake manifold, remove the following components:</para>
                <randlist type="bullet">
                    <item>
                        <para>Fuel Filter Housing and Lines</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>VGT</para>
                    </item>
                </randlist>
                <para>See "Fuel System" and "Electronically Controlled VGT" sections for removal procedures.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <warning>
                <para>To prevent personal injury or death, wear safety glasses with side shields to protect eyes. Limit
                    compressed air pressure to 207 kPa (30 psi).
                </para>
            </warning>
            <caution>
                <para>To prevent engine damage, blow out or vacuum dirt and debris under the intake manifold. This
                    prevents dirt and debris from entering intake ports when the manifold is removed.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="f2650315" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd14/D1437.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Intake heat shield mounting nuts (right side)</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove two M6 intake heat shield nuts on the right side of the intake manifold.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove heat shield.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2650316" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figD14/D1458.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Dog point bolts stud bolts</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Bolt (M6 x 95 dog point) (11)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Bolt (M6 x 95) stud (5)</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove 11 dog point bolts and 5 stud bolts.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2650317" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd05/D0511A.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px"/>
            <caption>EGR coolant inlet coupling</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Index feature on coolant supply port cover</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Recess</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Single index mark</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Flat edge representing duel index marks</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Align single index mark (if visible) or one of the recesses on the end of the EGR inlet
                coolant coupling with index feature located on coolant supply port cover.
            </para>
            <para>This aligns the detentes inside the coupling with the raised slide-off area of the coolant supply
                port.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2650318" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd14/D1444.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
            <caption>EGR coolant inlet coupling removal from coolant supply port</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Index feature on EGR coolant supply cover</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Coolant supply port</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">EGR coolant inlet coupling</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Slide the coupling off the port.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Slide EGR coolant inlet coupling toward rear of engine, away from coolant supply port.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2650319" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd14/D1441.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
            <caption>V-clamp on EGR Cooler</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove V-clamp from EGR cooler.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2650320" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd14/D1440A.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Intake manifold and EGR cooler</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lift intake manifold assembly straight up to remove.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove and save steel gasket for EGR cooler.</para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The EGR cooler will be bolted to the intake manifold.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Put protective magnetic covers over intake ports in cylinder head .</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
